Former French Open champion Ana Ivanovic has retired from tennis at the age of 29, the Serbian said on Facebook on Wednesday.&#8220;There is no other way to say this. I have decided to retire from professional tennis. It was a difficult decision but there is so much to celebrate,&#8221; Ivanovic said.&#8220;Don&#8217;t be sad, be optimistic alongside me. My love and my greatest thank you to all of you,&#8221; said the former world number one who has dropped to 63rd in the rankings.-Reuters